## Structure

```
{{.ProjectName}}/                  # this working copy (NOT a git repo at the top level)
{{- range .Repos}}
- {{.Folder}}/               # native git repo
{{- end}}
- .workspace/             # AI dev workspace (see .workspace/INDEX.md)
```

Sibling `{{.ProjectName}}-meta/` is the git-versioned meta workspace. Everything you see here that is not a native repo is a symlink into it.

## Workflow

- Commit changes to the meta from `cd ../{{.ProjectName}}-meta && git ...`.
- Commit code changes inside the relevant native repo (`cd <repo> && git ...`).
- Spin up parallel work via `mws clone <name>` -- creates `{{.ProjectName}}-<name>/` next to this one, sharing the meta.
- Promote a file from this working copy into the meta (and into every peer) with `mws promote <path>`.

## Conventions

Project-specific conventions live under `.claude/rules/` and `.workspace/knowledge/`. Start there.
